<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef8ffba1-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2910"><num value="2910">§ 2910.</num><heading> Preemption of other Federal and State programs; applicability of provisions to amendments to orders</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idef8ffba2-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2910/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> Nothing in this chapter may be construed to preempt or supersede any other program relating to beef promotion organized and operated under the laws of the United States or any State.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idef8ffba3-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2910/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The provisions of this chapter applicable to the order shall be applicable to amendments to the order.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idef8ffba4-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/94/294/s11">Pub. L. 94–294, § 11</ref>, <date date="1976-05-28">May 28, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/535">90 Stat. 535</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/198/tXVI/s1601/b">Pub. L. 99–198, title XVI, § 1601(b)</ref>, <date date="1985-12-23">Dec. 23, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/1606">99 Stat. 1606</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idef8ffba5-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idef8ffba6-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idef8ffba7-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1985—<ref href="/us/pl/99/198">Pub. L. 99–198</ref> amended section generally, substituting administrative provisions for provisions relating to applicability of provisions to amendments to orders.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idef8ffba8-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="idef8ffba9-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1985 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/99/198">Pub. L. 99–198</ref> effective <date date="1986-01-01">Jan. 1, 1986</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/99/198/s1601/c">section 1601(c) of Pub. L. 99–198</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s2901">section 2901 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
